Florida Hillsborough County Sheriff's Deputy John Robert Kotfila Jr. died in head-on car crash in Florida back in March 2016. The six-year veteran was praised as a hero by motorist Sarah Geren. Geren said she was about to be hit by a driver, Erik Thomas McBeth, who was going the wrong way up a highway when Kotfila save her. Kotfila accelerated in front of her car and used himself as a human shield. McBeth and Kotfila were both killed in the accident. Praising the officer, who is the third generation in his family to serve as a police officer, Geren said: "He saved my life."
